{
  "text": "by using Wick's theorem, the expression for the imaginary-time two-point functions and condition (4.1), in the same way as it is done, for instance, in [CITATION_1] , Thm IV.3. A similar argument shows that \u2200\u03d5 \u2208 D, {\u0393 n \u03d5} is a Cauchy sequence as n \u2192 0 and therefore \u0393 n \u03d5 converges as n \u2192 \u221e, which completes the proof of (4.26) and (4.27).",
